# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Where's My Context — configuration
# Copy to `.env` and fill in to enable a real Cognee memory backend.
# With NOTHING set, the app runs on the built-in Demo Engine.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# --- Option A: Cognee Cloud (managed memory) ---------------------
# Recommended for the hackathon. Get a key from the Cognee Cloud dashboard.
# MEMORY_ENGINE=cognee_cloud
# COGNEE_API_KEY=ck_your_cloud_api_key
# COGNEE_BASE_URL=https://api.cognee.ai      # or your https://<instance>.cognee.ai

# --- Option B: Self-hosted Cognee server -------------------------
# Point at a running Cognee API (the official plugin's local API is :8011).
# MEMORY_ENGINE=cognee
# COGNEE_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8011
# COGNEE_API_KEY=                            # not needed for a local single-user server

# The app talks to Cognee's memory-native REST API:
#   POST /api/v1/remember   (add + cognify)
#   POST /api/v1/recall     (search)
# — the same contract used by Cognee's official Claude Code plugin.

# --- Server ---
# PORT=8000
# SEED_ON_START=1                            # 0 to start empty
